    "course_title": "LITERATURE & CULTURE OF ASIAN AMERICA",
    "description": "Since the 19th century, \"America\" has often been defined by its relationship with \"Asia,\" through cultural influence, immigration, imperialism, and war. Traces the role of Asia and Asians in American literature and culture, from the Chinese and Japanese cultural influences that helped shape literary modernism to the rise of a distinctive culture produced by Asian immigrants to America and their descendants.",
